Hey Elena and Riley,
Thanks for sailing Greta back to Europe.
I'm also a sailor with a few Atlantic crossings to my names, so I know how tough it is to sail across the Atlantic at that time of the year.

The last of my Atlantic crossing was on a 42 foot cat, two handed with my son, who is also a climate activist, only a couple of weeks older than Greta.
He was very happy to welcome her in Madrid when she arrived. It couldn't have happened without you.

snippet.textDisplay:
The world's population is inevitably heading for eleven billion people by the end of this century; most of that coming out of sub Sahara Africa - the poorest countries on earth, with no ability or provision for their people and certainly no rights for women (hence the reason their population is exploding). Funny how no one is bothering to even mention this; as a planet wide disaster that will happen, unlike climate change which might or might not be a problem (plants love CO2)

And let's not forget; the west was in population decline until we decided to flood ourselves with foreigners (apparently they're great for the economy - those same economies that, in spite of being the largest in the world, are completely broke and running structural deficits - it's almost as if they're being mismanaged by idiots). Now we suddenly need to feel guilty about our carbon emissions? Yeah, I'm starting to get seriously tired of the liberal left; crusading for their next, trendy, utterly misguided, vanity project. Sail "school dropout" Greta around the coast of Africa and let her burst into tears whilst shouting at black men to stop making unwanted babies and see how you get on. But please, don't let the facts get in the way of your trendy narrative.

PS Hasn't Australia recently ramped up coal exports by six times to Asian countries? You're showboating in the wrong ocean. Have Trump onboard as your next guest and get the other side of the story.
